  "original_title": "\u0db6\u0dc3\u0dca \u0d9c\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4 \u0d85\u0da9\u0dd4 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dda \u0db8\u0dd9\u0dc4\u0dd9\u0db8\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "This is how the bus fares will be reduced",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Dr. Nilan Miranda, director of the National Transport Commission, says that the reduced public passenger transport bus fares will be effective from 12 midnight today (19) due to the decrease in fuel prices. The director stated this while joining the news conference held today (19) at the government news department auditorium to inform the people about the new bus fare revision plan.",
        "Due to the reduction in diesel price by Rs.20, the public passenger transport bus fare has been reduced by 2.23%. The current minimum fee of Rs.40 will be reduced to Rs.38. This applies to over 350 journeys across the island.",
        "The bus fare revision is applicable for all transport services like semi-luxury, luxury, ultra-luxury, high-speed ultra-luxury. All Sri Lanka Transport Board and private passenger buses are subject to it and the amendment is also applicable to all provincial and inter-provincial travel times.",
        "The price revision should be displayed on every bus. Complaints can be made by intimation to the hotline number 1955 if the relevant travel fare of a public passenger vehicle is not reduced from midnight today. Apart from this, mobile inspectors have also been deployed for this purpose. Simultaneously, student bus fares will also be reduced by 2.23%."
      ],
